System configuration:

	Solaris system using POSIX threads for co-expression switching

Latest Icon version:

	Version 9.4.1

Installer:

	Gregg Townsend
	Icon Project
	The University of Arizona

Missing features:

	None

Known bugs:

	Pthreads implementations are more sensitive than others to the
	accumulation of uncollected co-expressions when programs create
	many of them.  The message "System error ... cannot create thread"
	is symptomatic of this problem.

Comments:

	Tested on SPARC architecture running Solaris 2.6.

Date:

	November 30, 2001
